51
00:02:27,781 --> 00:02:30,083
Oh, from Master Gali.

52
00:02:30,083 --> 00:02:32,786
The rebels who are causing
trouble for Master Moo

53
00:02:32,786 --> 00:02:36,456
have set out to sea on
Pirate Horn's ship, Master.

54
00:02:36,456 --> 00:02:37,457
What?

55
00:02:37,457 --> 00:02:39,593
Guji, your orders
are to find them.

56
00:02:39,593 --> 00:02:42,696
You must not
let them get away.

57
00:02:42,696 --> 00:02:46,266
Leave it to us,
we will find them, Guji.

58
00:02:46,266 --> 00:02:48,068
(growling)

59
00:02:48,068 --> 00:02:52,039
All right, and make sure
you get that pirate, Horn.

60
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:53,707
Depart, Zilla.

61
00:02:53,707 --> 00:02:54,608
(growling)

62
00:02:54,608 --> 00:02:58,545
(evil laughter)

63
00:02:58,545 --> 00:03:04,217
And so, Horn, we will
finally meet again.

64
00:03:04,217 --> 00:03:06,453
Ya‐hoo!

65
00:03:06,453 --> 00:03:12,192
♪

66
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:13,827
(giggling)

67
00:03:13,827 --> 00:03:16,430
Chi, it's big!

68
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:18,432
And wide, chi.

69
00:03:18,432 --> 00:03:22,736
This is a promise, Phoenix,
we're gonna find you this time.

70
00:03:22,736 --> 00:03:24,304
Chi!

71
00:03:24,304 --> 00:03:27,007
(laughing)

72
00:03:27,007 --> 00:03:32,112
Uh, now how did they
get off work when we can't?

73
00:03:32,112 --> 00:03:36,717
Yes, well Mocchi's
never seen the sea, right?

74
00:03:36,717 --> 00:03:41,288
How long does this deck
swabbing business go on anyway?

75
00:03:41,288 --> 00:03:43,323
Suezo, you big lug!

76
00:03:43,323 --> 00:03:46,126
Are you slacking off again?

77
00:03:46,126 --> 00:03:50,030
You pirate, we're
passengers here, remember!

78
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:53,400
Where do you get off
ordering us around, Horn?

79
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:57,104
Captain‐‐I'm the
captain of this ship!

80
00:03:57,104 --> 00:03:58,805
You're a pirate!

81
00:03:58,805 --> 00:04:00,574
You're an eyeball!

82
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:03,643
Come on, Suezo, stop it.

83
00:04:03,643 --> 00:04:06,179
Ahoy there, sweetie.

84
00:04:06,179 --> 00:04:11,551
Oh, she doth teach the
torches to burneth bright.

85
00:04:11,551 --> 00:04:14,287
Beauty too rich for use.

86
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:16,456
‐For there‐‐
‐Hey, knock it off,

87
00:04:16,456 --> 00:04:20,093
you one‐eyed, no‐good,
sea slurpin' pirate!

88
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:23,697
Look, landlubber,
it's like I be tellin' ya,

89
00:04:23,697 --> 00:04:26,566
Captain Horn be
an honorable pirate.

90
00:04:26,566 --> 00:04:28,401
Watch, swabbies?

91
00:04:28,401 --> 00:04:30,003
Aye‐aye!

92
00:04:30,003 --> 00:04:31,204
(laughing)

93
00:04:31,204 --> 00:04:35,709
Yes, sir, I've always said
Captain Horn is a fine fellow.

94
00:04:35,709 --> 00:04:38,578
Come on, let me see.

95
00:04:38,578 --> 00:04:41,348
Wow, awesome!

96
00:04:41,348 --> 00:04:43,917
Well now, this old treasure?

97
00:04:43,917 --> 00:04:48,321
It just be a small indication of
my esteem for Miss Holly here.

98
00:04:48,321 --> 00:04:51,691
Horn, it's nothing
but a box of garbage.

99
00:04:51,691 --> 00:04:54,094
Cheap, trashy garbage.

100
00:04:54,094 --> 00:04:56,797
Huh, what'd you say?

101
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:58,532
Hah, you heard me!

102
00:04:58,532 --> 00:05:01,368
Please, stop arguing!

103
00:05:01,368 --> 00:05:04,237
(sail flapping)

104
00:05:04,237 --> 00:05:06,506
‐Listen.
‐Huh?

105
00:05:06,506 --> 00:05:09,142
It's awful quiet out there.

106
00:05:09,142 --> 00:05:10,610
Too quiet.

107
00:05:10,610 --> 00:05:12,512
♪

108
00:05:12,512 --> 00:05:15,882
Uh, I hate to bring this up,
but what do you want to bet

109
00:05:15,882 --> 00:05:19,186
that Moo controls
the ocean too?

110
00:05:19,186 --> 00:05:20,220
What?

111
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:22,756
Horn, it's safe, isn't it?

112
00:05:22,756 --> 00:05:24,457
I'm not one to brag,

113
00:05:24,457 --> 00:05:28,128
but there's not a safer
captain on these waters.

114
00:05:28,128 --> 00:05:32,065
I'll get the seven of you
to where you're going.

115
00:05:32,065 --> 00:05:35,869
Hmm‐‐one, two, three,
four, five, six...

116
00:05:35,869 --> 00:05:37,504
One, two, three,
four, five, six.

117
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:40,540
Hold on, a swabbie's missing!

118
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:41,641
Chi.

119
00:05:41,641 --> 00:05:47,547
♪

120
00:05:47,547 --> 00:05:51,785
Say there, I'll keelhaul ya!

121
00:05:51,785 --> 00:05:53,153
Swab the decks!

122
00:05:53,153 --> 00:05:56,523
The ocean's
not my thing, Captain.

123
00:05:56,523 --> 00:05:57,958
(laughs)

124
00:05:57,958 --> 00:06:01,494
Well, blow me down
and shiver me timbers, matey.

125
00:06:01,494 --> 00:06:03,597
All hands aloft.

126
00:06:03,597 --> 00:06:04,431
Ho!

127
00:06:04,431 --> 00:06:06,933
He's afraid of the water.

128
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:09,569
(laughing)

129
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:12,572
Horn, put him down!

130
00:06:12,572 --> 00:06:13,907
♪

131
00:06:13,907 --> 00:06:18,979
One, two, three!

132
00:06:18,979 --> 00:06:21,915
(yelling)

133
00:06:21,915 --> 00:06:25,719
♪

134
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:28,421
(splash)

135
00:06:28,421 --> 00:06:29,823
Golem, no!

136
00:06:29,823 --> 00:06:31,758
(laughing)

137
00:06:31,758 --> 00:06:34,761
Face your fears, that's
what me mother always said.

138
00:06:34,761 --> 00:06:36,663
And‐‐hmm?

139
00:06:36,663 --> 00:06:38,064
Uh‐oh.

140
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:41,434
Hold on, Golem,
I'll save you.

141
00:06:41,434 --> 00:06:43,303
Alley oop!

142
00:06:43,303 --> 00:06:55,849
♪

143
00:06:55,849 --> 00:06:58,118
All right, now pull!

144
00:06:58,118 --> 00:07:04,057
And pull, and pull, and pull.

145
00:07:04,057 --> 00:07:07,160
Are you two all right?

146
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,295
Ugh.

147
00:07:08,295 --> 00:07:10,397
That wasn't
a good idea, Horn.

148
00:07:10,397 --> 00:07:13,233
Ah, I see, rock.

149
00:07:15,001 --> 00:07:19,806
Well then, you just
stay here and rest a while.

150
00:07:19,806 --> 00:07:20,807
Thanks.

151
00:07:20,807 --> 00:07:22,642
No need to thank me, lad.

152
00:07:22,642 --> 00:07:26,980
Besides, Suezo will take
your share of the chores.

153
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:28,782
Hey, no way!

154
00:07:28,782 --> 00:07:32,218
There's penalties
for mutiny aboard my ship!

155
00:07:32,218 --> 00:07:33,486
Make my day.

156
00:07:33,486 --> 00:07:39,192
Oh, all right, but just know
that this is under duress!

157
00:07:39,192 --> 00:07:50,570
♪

158
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:52,372
Hard to starboard.

159
00:07:52,372 --> 00:07:54,674
Aye‐aye, Captain.

160
00:07:54,674 --> 00:07:57,510
♪

161
00:07:57,510 --> 00:08:01,848
Some monsters do anything
to get out of work.

